article.headline: Tulsa 69, Marshall 50
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Jerome Jordan scored a career-high 25 points and snared 10 rebounds to lead Tulsa to a 69-50 win over Marshall on Saturday. Tulsa's 7-foot junior center scored the Golden Hurricane's first eight points, reached double figures in the first eight minutes and had 16 by halftime as Tulsa (12-6, 2-1 Conference USA) opened up a 37-21 lead. Jordan made 7 of 12 field-goal attempts and 11-of-12 free throws and added three blocked shots. Guard Damier Pitts led Marshall (8-9, 1-2) with 19 points, eight of those coming at the free-throw line. The Thundering Herd show a season-low 30 percent and were outrebounded 41-23. Ben Uzoh, who had 16 points, four rebounds and three assists, limped off with 4:43 left after being fouled underneath. Tulsa coach Doug Wojcik said Uzoh had a slight ankle sprain.
